                                                                <div data-widget-id="wid__text__5f4e4cee46468" class="moto-widget moto-widget-text moto-preset-default  moto-spacing-top-small moto-spacing-right-auto moto-spacing-bottom-large moto-spacing-left-auto  " data-widget="text" data-preset="default" data-spacing="sala" data-visible-on="mobile-v" data-animation="">
                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Where can I go from Your Spirit? Or where can I flee from Your presence? If I ascend into heaven, You are there; If I make my bed in hell, behold, You are there. If I take the wings of the morning, And dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea, Even there Your hand shall lead me, And Your right hand shall hold me.”
                                                                            <b>Psalms 139:7-10 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Am I a God near at hand,” says the LORD, “And not a God afar off? Can anyone hide himself in secret places, So I shall not see him?” says the LORD; “Do I not fill heaven and earth?” says the LORD.”
                                                                            <b>Jeremiah 23:23-24</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">I chuckle to myself when I occasionally pray, “Lord be present in this situation.” Why chuckle?  Because God is always nearer than we imagine Him to be.  Right present with us all the time.  He never goes away.  I/we experience His presence in prayer and meditation, yet we know next door, across town, in the next state, across the country, in a totally other country someone is praying and in God’s presence also, but I/we feel as if we are the only one.  How can He be with us and at the same time being attentive to so many others?
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">God is a spiritual being and is not confined as we are to time and space.  He is present in the fullest sense of His being in all places at the same time.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Whether we ascend to the highest point (heaven) or the lowest of lows (Sheol), He is present with us.  As the scripture says if we flee to the distant east, (the wings of the morning) or to the distant west, (the uttermost parts of the sea), He is there.  He is in every part of our day with us, in every thought.  Yes the good, the bad, and the indifferent.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Let’s take a deep breath... close our eyes...be still and experience Him.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Another characterization of His Omnipresent is His Transcendence.  To transcend means to be above, rise above.  This is the part of not understanding He is with me, and you at the very same time working for good on behalf of both of us. It is because He is <b>“I AM” </b>.
                                                                            Continuing in His Self-Existence.  We are His created beings.  From conception His Spirit formed us, knit us together, we are fearfully and wonderfully made.  God is in everything and is everywhere.  He is in heaven on His throne, He cloths the grass of the field, the lilies neither toil nor spin, His concern is for the sparrow that would fall to the ground.  How much is He with me...and YOU?
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Father today may we allow ourselves to be still today and know You are God, may we allow Your Holy Spirit’s presence into our perspective and hold tight to the knowledge of your presence each day allowing You full access to every chamber of our hearts that you may be glorified in and through us.  Amen!
                                                                        </p>
